article.headline: Cleveland St. 52, Delaware 40
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- J'Nathan Bullock scored 17 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Cleveland State defeated Delaware 52-40 on Saturday. The Vikings scored 20 points off turnovers by the Blue Hens but put no other players in double figures as they shot 36 percent from the field. Calvin Cannon led Delaware (8-18) with 11 points. The Blue Hens pulled out to a 16-12 lead in the middle of the first half. But the Vikings (10-15) went on a 9-2 run to build a narrow 21-18 lead at the half. Delaware shot just 30 percent from the field.
